The paper deals with statistical query complexity, which is a topic in computational learning theory and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of statistical queries also involves information theory (cs.IT). The problem of mean estimation is a fundamental problem in machine learning and statistics, and the paper provides upper and lower bounds on the complexity of this problem, which is a topic in theoretical machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with norms, which are a topic in computational geometry and optimization, falling under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with high-dimensional distributions, which is a topic in statistical inference and falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
